main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects were reported in Watertown, New York, on various dates in 1953 and 1956.
interesting points: A triangular shaped object with a bright white color and a red dot in the center was observed,The object changed size and appeared to move slowly while maintaining a steady elevation,Multiple witnesses, including a housewife and a production engineer, provided similar descriptions of the objects observed,Some preliminary conclusions suggested that the sightings could be attributed to the planet Venus, but no definitive identifications were made.
witness description: A housewife, a production engineer, and a high school student, all from Watertown.
